  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And so when she came as a cleaning lady, the manager-- the apartment manager-- was telling her that Alexander is hiding our Jews-- me.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So that gave us a danger signal that there is problem here.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I had to leave.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Alexander knew a place, a bakery, which took in people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so he took me to that bakery where I stayed, I think, one night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was terrible, terrible bomb-- air raid going on in this-- at night.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this whole building was going like an earthquake, like a 7.5 earthquake.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The whole building was just shaking and going, and in this bakery, besides me, I was the only child there, there was about 25 forced labor people who-- who escaped from forced labor camps, adult Jewish people would be there.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] then when the bombing came to a point where this-- everybody saw that the building going to collapse, all of them threw their bodies on top of me to protect me from dying.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if anybody would have died, they would have been first.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was also a very touching experience in my life.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Why?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think-- I think, and I don't want to make a prejudice statement, but-- but it is a prejudice statement when I say said I think Jewish people are brought up that they protect their kids to the extremes and willing to give their lives and sacrifice their lives to their kids or other people's kids.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I think because it's a way we are brought up, I think-- I think that was a natural instinct in them that this is like almost like a duty.",
      "word_count": 30
    }
  ],
